# *Epic 1: SAP Data Integration*

### *User Stories*

* As a user, I want the system to *connect to SAP*, so I can analyze master and transactional data.
* As a user, I want the system to *read SAP master and transactional data*, so I can assess compliance impact.
* As a user I want the system to treat SAP "material" and "product" terminology equivalently so that analysis is consistent and unified.
[[[* As a user, I want *EHS integration*, so I can expand regulatory checks.]]]

---

# *Epic 2: Object & Scope Selection*

### *User Stories*

* As a compliance analyst, I want to select which SAP object type to analyze (suppliers, products/materials, documents, BOM) so that the system evaluate the correct compliance scope(compliant, non-compliant or missing info).


---

# *Epic 3: Product & Material Compliance*

### *User Stories*


* As a user I want the system to identify material type (raw, semi-finished or finished) so that I can determine the current production stage/step.
* As a user I want to display and analyze multi-level BOM structure, so that I can understand material composition.
* As a user I want the system to compute compliance from sub-components, so that we can determine if the parent material is compliant or not.
---

# *Epic 4: Supplier Compliance & Activity*

### *User Stories*

* As a user, I want *transaction history for suppliers/materials* included, so I can assess relevance and business value.
* As a user, I want to know whether suppliers/products are *active or inactive*, so I focus only on relevant cases.


---

# *Epic 5: Market & Country Logic*

### *User Stories*

* As a user I want to use supplier's country/region when evaluating regulations, so that region-specific rules are applied correctly.
* As a user I want the system to consider the target market's country/region so that regulations are applied depending on export destinations.


---

# *Epic 6: Compliance Indicators*

### *User Stories*

* As a user, I want the system to *read compliance fields* from SAP, so I can leverage existing information.
* As a user, I want the tool to *interpret non-standard fields* (e.g., free-text “EUDR relevant”), so that I can determine the compliance of the component.


---

# *Epic 7: Transaction Relevance & Volume*

### *User Stories*

* As a user, I want to see *sales/purchase volumes and transaction frequency*, so I understand business impact.

---

# *Epic 8: Regulatory Configurator*

### *User Stories*

* As a user, I want a *configurator*, so that I can define criteria per regulation.
* As a user, I want the configurator to *support multiple regulations* (EUDR, CS3D/LkSG, Machinery, etc.), so I can use one tool for compliance checks.
[[[As a user, I want both *master-data checks* and optional *operational flow analysis*, so I can go from quick screening to deeper evaluation.]]]

