Here are the **shortened epics (1–2 sentences max)** with the **correct user stories listed underneath**.

---

# ✅ **Epic 1 — SAP Connectivity & Data Acquisition**

Enable the system to connect to SAP and extract all relevant master, transactional, and compliance-related data, ensuring consistent terminology and usable inputs for analysis.

**User Stories**

* Connect to SAP to analyze master and transactional data.
* Read SAP master and transactional data to assess compliance impact.
* Read compliance fields from SAP.
* Interpret non-standard fields (e.g., free-text “EUDR relevant”).
* Treat SAP "material" and "product" terminology equivalently for consistent analysis.

---

# ✅ **Epic 2 — Object Selection & Scope Definition**

Allow compliance analysts to choose the SAP object type to analyze so the system applies the correct compliance scope.

**User Stories**

* Select which SAP object type to analyze (suppliers, products/materials, documents, BOM).

---

# ✅ **Epic 3 — Material Classification & Structure Analysis**

Provide understanding of material characteristics and hierarchical structure so the system can evaluate production stages and component relationships.

**User Stories**

* Identify material type (raw, semi-finished, finished).
* Display and analyze multi-level BOM structure.
* Compute compliance of parent materials based on sub-components.

---

# ✅ **Epic 4 — Supplier & Material Relevance Assessment**

Ensure the system evaluates only meaningful cases by including usage history, activity status, and transaction volumes.

**User Stories**

* Include transaction history for suppliers/materials.
* Identify whether suppliers/products are active or inactive.
* Display sales/purchase volumes and transaction frequency.

---

# ✅ **Epic 5 — Region-Based Compliance Evaluation**

Incorporate geographic information into compliance logic so regulations can be applied based on supplier origin and target markets.

**User Stories**

* Use supplier’s country/region when evaluating regulations.
* Consider the target market’s country/region when applying regulations.

---

# ✅ **Epic 6 — Multi-Regulation Configurator**

Provide a configurable rule engine that supports criteria definition and analysis across multiple regulatory frameworks.

**User Stories**

* Provide a configurator to define criteria per regulation.
* Support multiple regulations (EUDR, CS3D/LkSG, Machinery, etc.).

---

